OL,6,FAccording to data from Direct Line,
OL,7,Fthere are 10,000 cases of tool theft
OL,8,Fin London each year, as ITV News
OL,9,Freporter Antoine Allen investigated.
OL,11,FFor many tradespeople, their tools are
OL,12,Ftheir livelihood.
OL,14,FBut across Britain, thieves are
OL,15,Fturning vans and building sites into
OL,16,Fprime targets, fueling an underground
OL,17,Feconomy where stolen power tools are
OL,18,Fbeing openly sold at boot sales with
OL,19,Flittle fear of consequence.
